<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="198" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,885,1270]" pageId="11" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1209,1234]" pageId="11" pageNumber="198">Remarks.</emphasis>
This subspecies was first described as an independent species by 
<bibRefCitation author="Makihara, H." box="[1134,1332,1209,1234]" journalOrPublisher="Special Issue to the Memory of Retirement of Emeritus Professor Michio Chujo" pageId="11" pageNumber="198" pagination="127 - 133" part="12" refString="Makihara, H. (1982) New longicorn beetles of the Ryukyus (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Special Issue to the Memory of Retirement of Emeritus Professor Michio Chujo: 127 - 133, 12 figs." title="New longicorn beetles of the Ryukyus (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae)" type="journal article" year="1982">Makihara (1982)</bibRefCitation>
, but the differences from 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": N. Ohbayashi" authorityYear="1964" box="[343,501,1245,1269]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Caraphia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepturoides">
<emphasis box="[343,501,1245,1269]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="198">C. lepturoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are slight and it is appropriate to treat the taxon as a subspecies.
</paragraph>
